true to his word. It was a beautiful, bounteous, blue day; the spangled sea 
calm and cool, and flatly stretching away, all round, to the horizon, like 
gold-beater’s skin hammered out to the extremest. Bobbing up and down in that 
sea, Pip’s ebon head showed like a head of cloves. No boat-knife was lifted 
when he fell so rapidly astern. Stubb’s inexorable back was turned upon him; 
